From: Lorenzo Bianconi <lorenzo@kernel.org>
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] wifi: mt76: connac: Guard a NULL HE capability

mt76_connac_get_he_phy_cap() can return NULL when a band has no HE
capability. Bail out before dereferencing it.

Signed-off-by: Lorenzo Bianconi <lorenzo@kernel.org>
---
--- a/mt76_connac_mcu.c
+++ b/mt76_connac_mcu.c
@@ -1441,6 +1441,8 @@ mt76_connac_mcu_uni_bss_he_tlv(struct m
 	struct bss_info_uni_he *he;
 
 	cap = mt76_connac_get_he_phy_cap(phy, vif);
+	if (!cap)
+		return;
 
 	he = (struct bss_info_uni_he *)tlv;
 	he->he_pe_duration = vif->bss_conf.htc_trig_based_pkt_ext;
